void SOCKNET::Channel::connect (  )  [virtual]

Connection of the channel to the peer node. The connection protocol is

  • 1/ establish connexion to the remote peer node
  • 2/ send my local rank (may be -1 if unknown) and the local port for accepting connexion
  • 3/ recv my local rank, the rank of the peer node and an ack. If one of the steps failed, the connexion failed. In case of success, the peer node of the channel contains the node number of the peer node. The routing table may be not be set before connexion. The method locks the _access_w mutex.
Exceptions:
ComFailure,code= FAIL if the connexion failed
ComFailure,code= BAD_ADDRESS if the host is unreachable
Net::InvalidArgument,if the url of the peer node is not defined

Implements SOCKNET::Connexion.

void SOCKNET::Channel::disconnect ( bool  force  )  [virtual]

Disconnect to remote peer node Disconnect first send a P_CLOSE request in order to inform the remote node that the socket will be locally closed. The reply is either '1' if the socket could be closed or '0' if not. If force is set to true then force the disconnection even if the remote peer node reply to not close it.

Implements SOCKNET::Connexion.
